best of parents,

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:26.080 align:middle line:84%
we inevitably got shamed for
displaying certain qualities

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:29.230 align:middle line:84%
and received the message
that something about us

00:08:29.230 --> 00:08:33.190 align:middle line:84%
was not OK, that something
was wrong with us,

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:34.330 align:middle line:90%
or that we were bad.

00:08:34.330 --> 00:08:35.700 align:middle line:90%
>> You greedy little toot.

00:08:35.700 --> 00:08:38.049 align:middle line:84%
How are you going to eat
all those before dinner?

00:08:38.049 --> 00:08:41.110 align:middle line:84%
>> These messages getting
ingrained in our subconscious

00:08:41.110 --> 00:08:46.030 align:middle line:84%
like a computer virus, altering
our perception of ourselves,

00:08:46.030 --> 00:08:49.030 align:middle line:84%
and wounding our
healthy sense of ego.

00:08:49.030 --> 00:08:52.120 align:middle line:84%
When we suppress any
of these qualities,

00:08:52.120 --> 00:08:55.120 align:middle line:84%
we are living in denial
of all of who we are.

00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:58.751 align:middle line:90%


00:08:58.751 --> 00:09:01.250 align:middle line:84%
>> And of course, it's different
based upon our environment.

00:09:01.250 --> 00:09:04.880 align:middle line:84%
If you're raised in a family
of blue collar workers

00:09:04.880 --> 00:09:07.530 align:middle line:84%
and you declare that you
want to play the piano

00:09:07.530 --> 00:09:10.640 align:middle line:84%
or you want to become an
artist, that artistic quality

00:09:10.640 --> 00:09:14.060 align:middle line:84%
will be negatively
received, and you may end up

00:09:14.060 --> 00:09:15.290 align:middle line:90%
having to suppress that.

00:09:15.290 --> 00:09:16.880 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand,
if you're raised

00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:19.310 align:middle line:84%
in a family of artists
and intellectuals

00:09:19.310 --> 00:09:23.570 align:middle line:84%
and you declare that you want
to start working on construction

00:09:23.570 --> 00:09:25.040 align:middle line:84%
or you want to be
really athletic,

00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:28.161 align:middle line:84%
that may also be
perceived of as negative.

00:09:28.161 --> 00:09:33.460 align:middle line:90%


00:09:33.460 --> 00:09:36.850 align:middle line:84%
>> We try with all our might
to pretend that we are not that

00:09:36.850 --> 00:09:38.290 align:middle line:90%
which we hate.

00:09:38.290 --> 00:09:42.250 align:middle line:84%
In fact, proving this
is an all-important task

00:09:42.250 --> 00:09:46.690 align:middle line:84%
for the wounded ego, a
task which the ego believes

00:09:46.690 --> 00:09:49.360 align:middle line:90%
is vital to its existence.

00:09:49.360 --> 00:09:51.820 align:middle line:84%
The wounded ego must
hide all that we

00:09:51.820 --> 00:09:55.120 align:middle line:84%
believe is unacceptable
about ourselves.

00:09:55.120 --> 00:09:58.780 align:middle line:84%
To accomplish this task,
it constructs a mask

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:03.970 align:middle line:84%
to prove to others that we are
not as defective, inferior,

00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:07.870 align:middle line:84%
worthless, and bad as
we might fear we are.

00:10:07.870 --> 00:10:10.750 align:middle line:10%
None of us likes to admit
that we have these flaws

00:10:10.750 --> 00:10:13.720 align:middle line:10%
and insecurities,
so to hide them,

00:10:13.720 --> 00:10:17.410 align:middle line:10%
we create a persona
at a very young age.

00:10:17.410 --> 00:10:21.190 align:middle line:10%
We start to wrap ourselves
up in a new package

00:10:21.190 --> 00:10:24.640 align:middle line:10%
that we believe will bring
us the love, attention,

00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:26.745 align:middle line:10%
and acceptance
that we hunger for.

00:10:26.745 --> 00:10:35.960 align:middle line:90%


00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:38.370 align:middle line:84%
We create personas so
that we can belong.

00:10:38.370 --> 00:11:04.410 align:middle line:90%


00:11:04.410 --> 00:11:09.760 align:middle line:84%
Most of us have a public
life and a secret life.

00:11:09.760 --> 00:11:21.280 align:middle line:90%


00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:24.320 align:middle line:84%
We work hard to feel
good about ourselves,

00:11:24.320 --> 00:11:26.610 align:middle line:84%
and a moment later,
we do something

00:11:26.610 --> 00:11:28.245 align:middle line:90%
to sabotage those good feelings.

00:11:28.245 --> 00:11:49.920 align:middle line:90%


00:11:49.920 --> 00:11:52.230 align:middle line:84%
We wear masks that we
believe will take us

00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:56.285 align:middle line:84%
where we want to go, and
these masks take many forms.

00:11:56.285 --> 00:12:55.980 align:middle line:90%


00:12:55.980 --> 00:12:57.470 align:middle line:90%
Which one do you wear?

00:12:57.470 --> 00:13:02.380 align:middle line:90%


00:13:02.380 --> 00:13:04.770 align:middle line:90%
Our masks become our prison.

00:13:04.770 --> 00:13:06.870 align:middle line:84%
Beneath the mask that
we show the world,

00:13:06.870 --> 00:13:08.940 align:middle line:90%
our wounded egos are in pain.

00:13:08.940 --> 00:13:12.870 align:middle line:84%
The parts of us that were
deemed bad and wrong by others

00:13:12.870 --> 00:13:15.840 align:middle line:84%
and now by ourselves
are literally

00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:18.690 align:middle line:84%
screaming to get
out, to be set free,

00:13:18.690 --> 00:13:23.790 align:middle line:84%
and to be accepted and loved as
a valuable part of who we are.

00:13:23.790 --> 00:13:26.160 align:middle line:84%
When we deny ourselves
a safe outlet

00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:29.340 align:middle line:84%
to express our dark
side, it builds up

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:32.010 align:middle line:84%
and becomes a
powerful force that

00:13:32.010 --> 00:13:34.380 align:middle line:84%
is capable of
destroying our lives

00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:36.870 align:middle line:90%
as well as the lives of others.

00:13:36.870 --> 00:13:39.570 align:middle line:10%
This is what I call
the beach ball effect.

00:13:39.570 --> 00:13:43.980 align:middle line:10%
So everything that
we reject, we have

00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:48.840 align:middle line:10%
to keep beneath
our consciousness.

00:13:48.840 --> 00:13:50.970 align:middle line:90%
We try to bury it, so to speak.

00:13:50.970 --> 00:13:52.740 align:middle line:84%
You know how much
energy it takes

00:13:52.740 --> 00:13:54.900 align:middle line:90%
to put a beach ball underwater?

00:13:54.900 --> 00:13:57.870 align:middle line:84%
You take your selfish self,
you take your angry self,

00:13:57.870 --> 00:14:00.990 align:middle line:84%
you take your too good self,
your not good enough self,

00:14:00.990 --> 00:14:02.310 align:middle line:90%
you take all of it.

00:14:02.310 --> 00:14:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's like you have 40 beach
balls you're trying to manage.

00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:08.630 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens when
you're holding that beach ball

00:14:08.630 --> 00:14:09.480 align:middle line:90%
underwater?

00:14:09.480 --> 00:14:11.690 align:middle line:84%
When you're young, you've
got lots of energy,

00:14:11.690 --> 00:14:14.880 align:middle line:84%
so you can manage a
lot of beach balls.

00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:19.050 align:middle line:84%
But then when you're not in
the midst of possibility,

00:14:19.050 --> 00:14:23.310 align:middle line:84%
when your defenses are down,
when you have your attention

00:14:23.310 --> 00:14:27.310 align:middle line:84%
on some big prize you're going
to win, all of a sudden, boom!

00:14:27.310 --> 00:14:28.950 align:middle line:90%
Somebody does something.

00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:30.930 align:middle line:90%
What happens to the beach ball?

00:14:30.930 --> 00:14:33.250 align:middle line:84%
Pops up and it hits
you in the face.

00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:34.620 align:middle line:90%
What's road rage?

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:38.460 align:middle line:84%
Is it anything more than
that each ball coming up?

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.650 align:middle line:84%
We see it in the
media all the time.

00:14:40.650 --> 00:14:44.310 align:middle line:84%
A filmmaker is making
deep Christian films.

00:14:44.310 --> 00:14:48.000 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden gets drunk,
shouts anti-Semitic comments

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:49.440 align:middle line:90%
in a drunken rage, right?

00:14:49.440 --> 00:14:54.240 align:middle line:84%
A radio star makes his living
being a great communicator.

00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:57.700 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, makes a
comment, a racial slur.

00:14:57.700 --> 00:15:02.650 align:middle line:84%
So all of these beach balls
that you are trying to manage,

00:15:02.650 --> 00:15:05.580 align:middle line:90%
are you successful at it?

00:15:05.580 --> 00:15:06.550 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:09.130 align:middle line:90%
It's all, but not anymore.

00:15:09.130 --> 00:15:12.490 align:middle line:84%
>> When you don't deal with the
shadow, that part comes out,

00:15:12.490 --> 00:15:13.940 align:middle line:90%
and it'll creep up.

00:15:13.940 --> 00:15:15.740 align:middle line:90%
It'll creep up in workplaces.

00:15:15.740 --> 00:15:17.440 align:middle line:84%
It can creep up
in relationships.

00:15:17.440 --> 00:15:21.370 align:middle line:84%
>> The more we try to suppress
those societally determined

00:15:21.370 --> 00:15:25.300 align:middle line:84%
undesirable qualities, the
more they find interesting,

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:27.880 align:middle line:84%
often mischievous ways
to express themselves.

00:15:27.880 --> 00:15:31.390 align:middle line:84%
>> And it would be like locking
somebody in the basement who

00:15:31.390 --> 00:15:32.890 align:middle line:90%
wants to get out.

00:15:32.890 --> 00:15:34.810 align:middle line:84%
So they do things
down there to get

00:15:34.810 --> 00:15:38.710 align:middle line:84%
our attention until we
recognize them and let them out.

00:15:38.710 --> 00:15:41.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Because those aspects of
ourselves that we don't like

00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:43.300 align:middle line:84%
exit through a kind
of detox process.

00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:46.140 align:middle line:84%
It's got to come out in
order to be released.

00:15:46.140 --> 00:15:48.790 align:middle line:84%
>> One of my beach balls
happened in front of a room

00:15:48.790 --> 00:15:50.130 align:middle line:90%
full of people.

00:15:50.130 --> 00:15:53.370 align:middle line:84%
So I'm out of
treatment five years.

00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:56.290 align:middle line:84%
I've been floating
around, trying to become

00:15:56.290 --> 00:15:58.930 align:middle line:90%
the most perfect person.

00:15:58.930 --> 00:16:01.660 align:middle line:84%
How could I have people
want to be my friend?

00:16:01.660 --> 00:16:04.330 align:middle line:84%
How could I be a
little more spiritual?

00:16:04.330 --> 00:16:06.220 align:middle line:84%
I was on a quest,
and I thought I was

00:16:06.220 --> 00:16:08.340 align:middle line:90%
doing a really beautiful job.

00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:10.480 align:middle line:90%
And I went to another workshop.

00:16:10.480 --> 00:16:12.460 align:middle line:84%
We had to get up in
front of the room

00:16:12.460 --> 00:16:15.100 align:middle line:84%
and say what we were
committed to in the world.

00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:17.450 align:middle line:84%
And I thought I was
just being wonderful,

00:16:17.450 --> 00:16:20.460 align:middle line:84%
and everybody was looking at me
like, you're all looking at me.

00:16:20.460 --> 00:16:23.650 align:middle line:84%
And from the back of the
room this woman screams out,

00:16:23.650 --> 00:16:24.700 align:middle line:90%
you're a bitch!

00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:28.240 align:middle line:90%


00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:30.970 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
well, I know that.

00:16:30.970 --> 00:16:31.960 align:middle line:90%
How does she know?

00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:33.570 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:33.570 --> 00:16:35.270 align:middle line:90%
And I was horrified.

00:16:35.270 --> 00:16:36.970 align:middle line:90%
I was so humiliated.

00:16:36.970 --> 00:16:40.540 align:middle line:84%
It was the one word that I
didn't want to be called.

00:16:40.540 --> 00:16:42.970 align:middle line:84%
And she said to me,
tell me something good

00:16:42.970 --> 00:16:45.145 align:middle line:90%
about being a bitch.

00:16:45.145 --> 00:16:46.520 align:middle line:84%
And I said, there's
nothing good.

00:16:46.520 --> 00:16:47.811 align:middle line:90%
She goes, well, you're a bitch.

00:16:47.811 --> 00:16:50.830 align:middle line:84%
There's got to be something
good about being a bitch.

00:16:50.830 --> 00:16:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And all I could think of was all
the ways that that part of me

00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:57.030 align:middle line:90%
had hurt me.

00:16:57.030 --> 00:16:59.080 align:middle line:84%
And at the time,
I was a retailer.

00:16:59.080 --> 00:17:01.780 align:middle line:84%
And she said, do you ever
get damaged merchandise

00:17:01.780 --> 00:17:03.520 align:middle line:90%
delivered to your store?

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:05.050 align:middle line:90%
And I said, all the time.

00:17:05.050 --> 00:17:07.630 align:middle line:84%
She said, is there ever a
time where they don't want

00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:09.650 align:middle line:90%
to take back the damaged goods?

00:17:09.650 --> 00:17:10.540 align:middle line:90%
And I said, yes.

00:17:10.540 --> 00:17:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
do you ever have

00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:15.300 align:middle line:84%
to get a little forceful
or a little bitchy?

00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:17.859 align:middle line:90%
And I said, oh my god, yes.

00:17:17.859 --> 00:17:19.900 align:middle line:84%
And I was remodeling
a house at the time.

00:17:19.900 --> 00:17:22.819 align:middle line:84%
She said, when you're
a couple of weeks late

00:17:22.819 --> 00:17:26.890 align:middle line:84%
and $20,000 over budget, does
it help to be a little bitchy?

00:17:26.890 --> 00:17:28.810 align:middle line:90%
Would it help you?

00:17:28.810 --> 00:17:31.000 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, I
realized that when I finally

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:34.300 align:middle line:84%
said to the contractor, you
need to finish my house,

00:17:34.300 --> 00:17:36.040 align:middle line:90%
he finished my house.

00:17:36.040 --> 00:17:39.190 align:middle line:84%
And this light went
on inside of me

00:17:39.190 --> 00:17:41.200 align:middle line:84%
that this part of me
that I had shamed,

00:17:41.200 --> 00:17:45.940 align:middle line:84%
that I had hated so much,
actually came bearing gifts.

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:49.990 align:middle line:84%
She said, either
you're going to use it,

00:17:49.990 --> 00:17:52.510 align:middle line:90%
or it's going to use you.

00:17:52.510 --> 00:17:56.310 align:middle line:84%
And that was a
life-changing moment for me.

00:17:56.310 --> 00:17:59.470 align:middle line:84%
>> When we fully
understand the human soul,

00:17:59.470 --> 00:18:03.730 align:middle line:84%
we find that it's a place of
ambiguity, of contradiction,

00:18:03.730 --> 00:18:04.960 align:middle line:90%
of paradox.

00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:11.230 align:middle line:84%
All experience is a result of
contrast, light and shadow,

00:18:11.230 --> 00:18:14.950 align:middle line:84%
pleasure and pain, up and
down, backwards and forwards.

00:18:14.950 --> 00:18:19.570 align:middle line:84%
In order to have manifestation,
you need opposing energies.

00:18:19.570 --> 00:18:22.570 align:middle line:84%
You need your enemies
to be who you are.

00:18:22.570 --> 00:18:25.780 align:middle line:84%
The human soul is simultaneously
divine and diabolical,

00:18:25.780 --> 00:18:28.540 align:middle line:84%
sacred and profane,
a sinner and saint.

00:18:28.540 --> 00:18:30.590 align:middle line:84%
Eastern wisdom traditions,
we have a saying.

00:18:30.590 --> 00:18:33.760 align:middle line:84%
The sinner and saint are
merely exchanging notes.

00:18:33.760 --> 00:18:37.090 align:middle line:84%
So once you understand that,
then first thing you realize

00:18:37.090 --> 00:18:38.725 align:middle line:90%
is to have a shadow is normal.

00:18:38.725 --> 00:18:41.500 align:middle line:84%
If you had only truth,
goodness, harmony on your side

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:43.680 align:middle line:84%
and the complete
absence of the other,

00:18:43.680 --> 00:18:45.490 align:middle line:84%
there would be no
creative impulse.

00:18:45.490 --> 00:18:48.420 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you're only the
evolutionary creative impulse

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:49.310 align:middle line:90%
in the universe.

00:18:49.310 --> 00:18:51.580 align:middle line:84%
Then the universe would
rapidly burn itself

00:18:51.580 --> 00:18:55.810 align:middle line:84%
into the heat death
of absolute zero.

00:18:55.810 --> 00:18:57.360 align:middle line:84%
If, on the other
hand, you're only

00:18:57.360 --> 00:19:00.820 align:middle line:84%
the impulse of inertia or
destruction or entropy,

00:19:00.820 --> 00:19:04.390 align:middle line:84%
then the universe would rapidly
collapse into a big black hole

00:19:04.390 --> 00:19:07.260 align:middle line:84%
before you could
say Deepak Chopra.

00:19:07.260 --> 00:19:11.140 align:middle line:84%
>> We are the microcosm
of the macrocosm.

00:19:11.140 --> 00:19:15.490 align:middle line:84%
This means that every quality
that we can see in another

00:19:15.490 --> 00:19:17.680 align:middle line:90%
exists within us.

00:19:17.680 --> 00:19:21.920 align:middle line:84%
We possess every human
characteristic and emotion,

00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:24.460 align:middle line:84%
whether active or
dormant, whether

00:19:24.460 --> 00:19:27.010 align:middle line:90%
conscious or unconscious.

00:19:27.010 --> 00:19:32.530 align:middle line:84%
There is nothing we can see or
conceive of that we are not.

00:19:32.530 --> 00:19:36.970 align:middle line:84%
We are everything, that
which we consider good

00:19:36.970 --> 00:19:39.910 align:middle line:90%
and that which we consider bad.

00:19:39.910 --> 00:19:43.750 align:middle line:84%
How could we know courage
if we have never known fear?

00:19:43.750 --> 00:19:47.920 align:middle line:84%
How could we know happiness
if we never knew sadness?

00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:51.910 align:middle line:84%
How could we know the light
if we didn't know dark?

00:19:51.910 --> 00:19:54.790 align:middle line:84%
All of life is based
on the coexistence

00:19:54.790 --> 00:19:58.250 align:middle line:90%
of these pairs of opposites.

00:19:58.250 --> 00:20:01.700 align:middle line:84%
Our shadow is forever
hiding from itself.

00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:04.190 align:middle line:84%
Rather than confront
our own darkness,

00:20:04.190 --> 00:20:08.660 align:middle line:84%
we project these unwanted
qualities onto others.

00:20:08.660 --> 00:20:10.890 align:middle line:10%
When we are projecting
our shadow selves,

00:20:10.890 --> 00:20:12.870 align:middle line:10%
it sounds like this.

00:20:12.870 --> 00:20:14.790 align:middle line:10%
She's so self-centered.

00:20:14.790 --> 00:20:16.680 align:middle line:10%
He's so full of himself.

00:20:16.680 --> 00:20:18.690 align:middle line:90%
These people are idiots.

00:20:18.690 --> 00:20:20.430 align:middle line:90%
What a loser.

00:20:20.430 --> 00:20:24.630 align:middle line:84%
Afraid of our own unworthiness
and simultaneously afraid

00:20:24.630 --> 00:20:27.870 align:middle line:84%
of our own greatness,
we unconsciously

00:20:27.870 --> 00:20:30.900 align:middle line:84%
transfer these
qualities onto another

00:20:30.900 --> 00:20:34.110 align:middle line:84%
rather than owning
them ourselves.

00:20:34.110 --> 00:20:38.820 align:middle line:84%
Those we project on own pieces
of our unclaimed darkness

00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:42.960 align:middle line:84%
as well as pieces of
our unclaimed light.

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:47.520 align:middle line:84%
Until we take back all that
we have projected away,

00:20:47.520 --> 00:20:51.170 align:middle line:84%
what we can't be
with won't let us be.

00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:58.950 align:middle line:90%


00:20:58.950 --> 00:21:01.740 align:middle line:84%
One of the most frequently
asked questions I get

00:21:01.740 --> 00:21:05.490 align:middle line:84%
is, how do you know
if you're projecting?

00:21:05.490 --> 00:21:07.350 align:middle line:90%
If it's your stuff or theirs?

00:21:07.350 --> 00:21:10.620 align:middle line:84%
I think it was best said
by revered philosopher

00:21:10.620 --> 00:21:12.480 align:middle line:90%
and psychologist Ken Wilber.

00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:15.720 align:middle line:84%
He says that if a person or
a thing in our environment

00:21:15.720 --> 00:21:20.840 align:middle line:84%
informs us, if we receive what
is happening as information,

00:21:20.840 --> 00:21:24.090 align:middle line:84%
a point of interest, we
probably aren't projecting.

00:21:24.090 --> 00:21:27.120 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand,
if it affects us--

00:21:27.120 --> 00:21:31.230 align:middle line:84%
we're pointing our fingers,
judging, if we're plugged in--

00:21:31.230 --> 00:21:36.650 align:middle line:84%
chances are that we are a
victim of our own projections.

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:40.890 align:middle line:84%
Think of someone from your
own life who disgusts, annoys,

00:21:40.890 --> 00:21:44.390 align:middle line:84%
or repulses you, and think
of the qualities about them

00:21:44.390 --> 00:21:45.920 align:middle line:90%
that you most hate.

00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:49.570 align:middle line:84%
Now imagine this person
standing right in front of you.

00:21:49.570 --> 00:21:53.660 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to put your hand
out, point your finger at them,

00:21:53.660 --> 00:21:58.130 align:middle line:84%
and say, you're an idiot,
or you're are a know-it-all,

00:21:58.130 --> 00:21:59.810 align:middle line:90%
or you're selfish.

00:21:59.810 --> 00:22:01.820 align:middle line:90%
Now stop where you are.

00:22:01.820 --> 00:22:03.950 align:middle line:84%
Keep your finger
pointing at them,

00:22:03.950 --> 00:22:07.880 align:middle line:84%
and now notice that one finger
is pointing at them, and where

00:22:07.880 --> 00:22:10.460 align:middle line:84%
the other three
fingers pointing?

00:22:10.460 --> 00:22:12.020 align:middle line:90%
Back at you.

00:22:12.020 --> 00:22:14.900 align:middle line:84%
This is the phenomenon
of projection.

00:22:14.900 --> 00:22:17.780 align:middle line:84%
Instead of acknowledging
the qualities within us

00:22:17.780 --> 00:22:21.950 align:middle line:84%
that we dislike, we project
them onto someone else.

00:22:21.950 --> 00:22:26.600 align:middle line:84%
We project them onto our
mothers, our kids, our friends,

00:22:26.600 --> 00:22:30.230 align:middle line:84%
or even better, some
famous public figure

00:22:30.230 --> 00:22:34.130 align:middle line:90%
who we have never even met.

00:22:34.130 --> 00:22:37.790 align:middle line:84%
If I asked each of you what
you love about these people,

00:22:37.790 --> 00:22:41.230 align:middle line:84%
you would each have
a different response.

00:22:41.230 --> 00:22:45.290 align:middle line:84%
The people that you hate
also represent some aspect

00:22:45.290 --> 00:22:47.120 align:middle line:90%
of yourself that you don't own.

00:22:47.120 --> 00:22:49.310 align:middle line:84%
Notice what you
think and feel as you

00:22:49.310 --> 00:22:51.009 align:middle line:90%
look at each of these people.

00:22:51.009 --> 00:23:45.420 align:middle line:90%


00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:48.780 align:middle line:84%
Whatever we judge or
condemn in another

00:23:48.780 --> 00:23:54.113 align:middle line:84%
is ultimately a disowned or
rejected part of ourselves.

00:23:54.113 --> 00:23:57.430 align:middle line:90%


00:23:57.430 --> 00:24:01.220 align:middle line:84%
>> I was watching the events
of 9/11 on TV with a friend

00:24:01.220 --> 00:24:02.020 align:middle line:90%
of mine.

00:24:02.020 --> 00:24:04.450 align:middle line:84%
And after that, we were
driving down the street,

00:24:04.450 --> 00:24:08.830 align:middle line:84%
and turned to my friend and I
said, you know, from now on,

00:24:08.830 --> 00:24:10.960 align:middle line:84%
the Arabs are going
to be the new blacks.

00:24:10.960 --> 00:24:14.800 align:middle line:84%
They're going to get the
brunt of a lot of projections

00:24:14.800 --> 00:24:19.120 align:middle line:84%
that blacks have carried in
this culture for a long time.

00:24:19.120 --> 00:24:22.330 align:middle line:84%
Now a lot of times,
blacks react.

00:24:22.330 --> 00:24:26.650 align:middle line:84%
We react to those projections,
and we project back,

00:24:26.650 --> 00:24:28.610 align:middle line:84%
and that creates
a vicious cycle.

00:24:28.610 --> 00:24:32.350 align:middle line:84%
And the ego consciousness
just responds the way

00:24:32.350 --> 00:24:36.070 align:middle line:84%
it should, really, because
it's designed to respond

00:24:36.070 --> 00:24:37.600 align:middle line:90%
as a survival mechanism.

00:24:37.600 --> 00:24:40.210 align:middle line:84%
That's what the ego's all
about, to help us survive.

00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:41.480 align:middle line:90%
But it's mechanical.

00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:42.460 align:middle line:90%
It's reactive.

00:24:42.460 --> 00:24:47.320 align:middle line:84%
When an aggressive, negative
energy is directed at us,

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:50.680 align:middle line:84%
the ego immediately wants
to defend and react.

00:24:50.680 --> 00:24:53.230 align:middle line:84%
Of course, when you
react to a projection,

00:24:53.230 --> 00:24:55.540 align:middle line:90%
you become that projection.

