00:38:00.640 --> 00:38:03.200 align:middle line:84%
but internally, they do two
completely different things

00:38:03.200 --> 00:38:04.000 align:middle line:90%
with it.

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:05.599 align:middle line:84%
That's why we read
incredible stories

00:38:05.599 --> 00:38:07.390 align:middle line:84%
about people who went
through the Holocaust

00:38:07.390 --> 00:38:10.180 align:middle line:84%
or people who were
victims of genocide,

00:38:10.180 --> 00:38:11.350 align:middle line:90%
and yet they survived.

00:38:11.350 --> 00:38:13.510 align:middle line:84%
And yet, they go on to
live extraordinary lives.

00:38:13.510 --> 00:38:14.926 align:middle line:84%
And then you meet
other people who

00:38:14.926 --> 00:38:17.800 align:middle line:84%
went through a fraction of that
in terms of an internal trauma,

00:38:17.800 --> 00:38:19.720 align:middle line:84%
but they stay stuck
in it forever.

00:38:19.720 --> 00:38:21.820 align:middle line:84%
We begin to ask ourselves,
what am I getting

00:38:21.820 --> 00:38:23.260 align:middle line:90%
from staying stuck there?

00:38:23.260 --> 00:38:25.300 align:middle line:84%
What am I avoiding from
staying stuck there?

00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:28.450 align:middle line:84%
And what we are avoiding is
the greatest challenge of all,

00:38:28.450 --> 00:38:32.470 align:middle line:84%
and that is to be who we can
be in order to serve the world.

00:38:32.470 --> 00:38:36.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I asked a few people to
